HEADWORD: Retineum
<hw>Ret`i*ne"um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Retinea</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Retina</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>That part of the eye of
an invertebrate which corresponds in function with the retina of a
vertebrate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retinic</ent>⟦br⟧
